7647\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104doo1705564680445.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/doo1705564680445.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/doo1705564680445.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xwo1665702826218\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Executing Applications\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can execute the application using <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface.exe</span> or make a copy of <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface.exe</span> with your application name.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xwo1665702826218__li_d5987e1_d5988e1_d5989e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xwo1665702826218__p_d12668e1_d12669e1_d12670e1\">If required, create an <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span>\n               file and assignment file for the application.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">You can use the [APPLICATION] section in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file to\n               specify a custom icon and logo for the application.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xwo1665702826218__li_d5990e1_d5991e1_d5992e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xwo1665702826218__p_d12671e1_d12672e1_d12673e1\">Supply your application shell as a parameter when\n               running the Uniface runtime engine.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">uniface.exe myapp</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwo1665702826218__p_d12674e1_d12675e1_d12676e1\">Only <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface.exe</span> is capable\n                  of running an application if it is given as a parameter.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xwo1665702826218__li_d5993e1_d5994e1_d5995e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xwo1665702826218__p_d12677e1_d12678e1_d12679e1\">Alternatively, copy\n                  <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface.exe</span> to a file with the same name as your application. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, copy <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface.exe</span> to\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">myapp.exe</span>. When <span class=\"ph filepath\">myapp.exe</span> is\n                  executed, Uniface attempts to locate an application called <code class=\"ph codeph\">myapp</code>,\n                  with a <span class=\"ph filepath\">myapp.ini</span> file and an accompanying\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">myapp.asn</span> file (unless otherwise specified).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwo1665702826218__p_d12680e1_d12681e1_d12682e1\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">myapp.exe</span> executable\n                  cannot run another application if it is given as a parameter.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5827647\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5827647\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Executing Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Executing Applications You can execute the application using uniface.exe or make a copy of uniface.exe with your application name. If required, create an .ini file and assignment file for the application. You can use the [APPLICATION] section in the .ini file to specify a custom icon and logo for the application. Supply your application shell as a parameter when running the Uniface runtime engine. For example: uniface.exe myapp . Only uniface.exe is capable of running an application if it is given as a parameter. Alternatively, copy uniface.exe to a file with the same name as your application. For example, copy uniface.exe to myapp.exe . When myapp.exe is executed, Uniface attempts to locate an application called myapp , with a myapp.ini file and an accompanying myapp.asn file (unless otherwise specified). The myapp.exe executable cannot run another application if it is given as a parameter. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}